Siaya Governor Cornel Rasanga has started a drive to identify community health workers to campaign for him. The governor is trying to bring on board those capable of convincing voters at their doorsteps to re-elect him.Rasanga is also reaching out to MCAs from Rarieda, Gem, Bondo, Ugunja and Ugenya to popularise his candidature ahead of the ODM party primaries.On Wednesday, he dismissed his rivals as &ldquo;jokers&rdquo;, saying they have nothing to offer. &ldquo;I want to warn them that I&rsquo;m not a louse that hangs on a piece of cloth that could be controlled by anybody,&rdquo; Rasanga said.He said he will provide the CHWs with two kits of healthcare items and campaign tools to persuade residents to back him.